Senior QA Engineer for MarTech - Remote
GR8 Tech
is a global product company that provides innovative, scalable platforms and business solutions for the iGaming industry.
We have а great experience: GR8 Tech
platform successfully handles millions of active players and offers best practices to develop and grow in the gambling industry. We are here to provide great gaming tech to satisfy even greater ambition!
We develop complete tech coverage for gambling businesses worldwide, including iGaming platform solutions, consulting, integration, and long-lasting operation services.
We are driven by our ambition to make a great product with great people! Together we move the world of iGaming forward — join!
About your key responsibilities and impact:
Performing functional, and non-functional, regression testing;
Improving the testing process within the team;
Using and implementing new best practices in testing to ensure product quality and reliability;
Maximizing test coverage, preparing and maintaining test documentation including test cases, checklists, and bug reports;
Designing, writing and executing automated tests under the guidance of Automation QA;
Analyzing the requirements and communicating with stakeholders for clarification;
Сonducting bugs root cause analysis and propose preventive measures to improve product quality;
Participating in bug triage meetings;
Participating in testing processes during releases with other QA team members;
Proactive daily collaboration and communication with the QA team, Developers, PM, Product Managers, stakeholders;
Mentoring new Junior and Middle QA employees if needed.
Essential professional experience:
3+ years of experience in quality assurance, particularly in web testing;
Proficiency in different testing types and methods, including functional, performance, and regression testing;
Strong knowledge of REST API testing and tools such as Postman or similar;
Good SQL knowledge for database testing;
Automation testing experience, preferably using JavaScript, Cypress;
Hands-on experience with test management and bug reporting tools (e.g., Jira, TestRail);
Professional experience in creating and executing test cases;
Spoken and written Ukrainian and English (Upper-Intermediate level or above).
What we offer:
Benefits Cafeteria:
Sports compensation;
Medical coverage;
Psychological support;
Home-office coverage.
Work-life:
Remote work, Coworking compensation;
Childcare budget;
Maternity leave;
Paternity leave;
Additional 2 days for family events.
